1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,920
Kitti and Singha…

2
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,120
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:36,840
They're dealing drugs.

4
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,000
Hey, wait!

5
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:41,640
Leave that box. Unload the others.

6
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:43,960
All boxes are the same.

7
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,640
Not the same.

8
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,960
I said the other boxes.

9
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,400
Chart.

10
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,720
What are you guys looking for?

11
00:02:52,480 --> 00:02:53,600
Is it the guy with the limp?

12
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,120
-I saw him heading that way.
-Follow him.

13
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,880
Aren't you going to count it?

14
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:07,120
No need, sir. We trust you completely.

15
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,000
-Take cover!
-Go! Get down!

16
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:45,680
How did they know? Move!

17
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:59,040
Who were those guys?
How dare they attack here?

18
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:03,440
Just some petty criminals.

19
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:05,680
Still, I have to apologize

20
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:06,880
for the unexpected chaos.

21
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:11,320
No problem. I'll be going then.

22
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,000
Please go ahead.

23
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:13,920
Hey.

24
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,600
Nice work, Kitti.

25
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,040
That Khod guy is really useful.

26
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:34,680
If Pleaw finds out Khod's our informant,

27
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:36,680
he'll be furious.

28
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:42,080
For me, money can buy anything,

29
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,560
even loyalty.

30
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:50,440
We should get out of here.

31
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:53,160
Yeah, let's go back.

32
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:54,800
Move!

33
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,120
Boss.

34
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,280
I have something strange to report.

35
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:16,480
Go ahead.

36
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:19,880
About Tharin, Phupha's twin,

37
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:23,480
I remember you said

38
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:27,000
Phupha's great at fighting,

39
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:29,480
while his twin Tharin isn't.

40
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:33,400
But just now, that Tharin

41
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:34,880
took out my men completely.

42
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:36,640
-Really?
-It's true.

43
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,160
His skills aren't normal.

44
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:42,320
The two of us couldn't take him down.

45
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:51,200
Wait, Chart. Are you sure

46
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,240
it was really Tharin?

47
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,800
I saw his face clearly.

48
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,960
I remember him.

49
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:09,120
Chart, send someone to his house

50
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:11,760
and report back to me.

51
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,320
Yes, Boss.

52
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:49,320
<i>I've waited</i>

53
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:54,600
<i>Waited so long</i>
<i>My heart unwavering and full</i>

54
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:59,200
<i>But he's forgotten</i>

55
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:05,640
<i>Forgotten me, with no certainty at all</i>

56
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:10,520
<i>I wait for him, but he forgets I'm waiting</i>

57
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,600
<i>Waiting and pleading</i>

58
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:18,280
<i>With this lonely heart</i>

59
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:24,840
<i>Still waiting</i>

60
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:30,000
<i>I kept hoping until I grew weary</i>

61
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:34,880
<i>Still waiting</i>

62
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:36,360
<i>For that heartless one</i>

63
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:39,520
-<i>Crying day and night</i>
-Why's that voice so amazing?

64
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,240
Clear like a nightingale,

65
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:44,440
sharp like cut glass.
Whose daughter is that?

66
00:07:44,520 --> 00:07:46,440
Oh no, help!

67
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:49,000
Some pervert's trying
to steal my underwear!

68
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:51,440
Go! Get out!

69
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:54,840
Hey, why are you stealing my underwear?
I'm too old for this.

70
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,400
You pervert!

71
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,160
Hey! That's my husband's underwear.

72
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,520
Why are you taking my husband's underwear?

73
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,880
My goodness.

74
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,840
What's going on, Auntie?

75
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:06,760
Some pervert.

76
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,320
He keeps stealing underwear.

77
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:14,080
Every time I wash and hang
my underwear, it gets stolen.

78
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,600
Today's worse.

79
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,840
He stole my husband's underwear!

80
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,160
Your husband's underwear?

81
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,280
Yes!

82
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,480
What?

83
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,840
Really?

84
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:31,800
I followed them secretly

85
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,280
and took photos.

86
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,880
Just as you see from the ones I sent you.

87
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:40,400
That Singha and Kitti.

88
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,360
I can tolerate a lot of things,

89
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:48,200
but I will never forgive them
for the drugs.

90
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:53,840
Go tell Captain Tom I need to talk to him.

91
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:55,120
Yes, Kamnan.

92
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,360
Kamnan, you called me. What's going on?

93
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:08,120
I checked into the drug issue.

94
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,040
Everything is exactly as you said.

95
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,960
Don't worry about a thing.

96
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:27,720
I've planned to outsmart them.
Just waiting for them to drop their guard.

97
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:32,360
But I don't want Wilai involved
with these people anymore.

98
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:35,080
She's already been through enough pain.

99
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,160
That's exactly why I called for you.

100
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,720
What do you mean, Kamnan?

101
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,200
You having to suffer like this

102
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:57,960
is partly

103
00:09:58,720 --> 00:10:00,520
my fault.

104
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,160
You've suffered a lot already.

105
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,920
I just want to see you happy.

106
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,880
All of you! Stop right there!

107
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,960
Don't try to fight!

108
00:10:37,920 --> 00:10:38,960
Who are you guys?

109
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:39,960
Are you cops?

110
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:41,920
We're sugarcane cutters.

111
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:43,000
Me too.

112
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,600
Sugarcane cutters?

113
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:49,040
Sugarcane cutters like us
are here to catch you.

114
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,640
I've had the cyber team

115
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:34,600
trace the mysterious number already.

116
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,080
Whose number is it?

117
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:39,000
Not sure whose it is,

118
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:41,280
but the signal comes from around here.

119
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,200
BAN NERN MAKHAM

120
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:47,880
What's in that area?

121
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,600
Nern Makham rental house.

122
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,640
Tomorrow, we will check it out ourselves.

123
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:00,520
The rental house in Nern Makham?

124
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,400
That thug.

125
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,600
Could he be the one
who tipped us off about the drugs?

126
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:50,040
Who are they?

127
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,440
They look familiar.

128
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,240
I'm outta here!

129
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:09,040
Who are you guys?

130
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,560
Let me go!

131
00:13:20,160 --> 00:13:21,800
Stay still. Don't struggle.

132
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,240
So it really is your number.

133
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:44,960
My calls weren't getting through earlier.
You had your phone off, huh?

134
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:50,000
What now? The evidence is right here.
Still gonna try to deny it?

135
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:51,760
Huh?

136
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:57,040
Yeah, it's my number.
I was the one who tipped off the police.

137
00:13:57,120 --> 00:14:00,400
Why did you suddenly inform the police?

138
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,400
What happened?

139
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:05,200
I wanted the cops to throw all those scum

140
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,760
in jail.

141
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:12,240
Both Singha and Boss Noo.

142
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:16,280
I wanted them to rot in prison,

143
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:18,360
dead and gone!

144
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,280
Do you know?

145
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,680
I've had to live
hiding like this all this time

146
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:24,280
because of those two!

147
00:14:31,200 --> 00:14:32,320
What did they do?

148
00:14:32,400 --> 00:14:34,240
Why should I tell you?

149
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,800
You think I'm stupid?

150
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:37,760
You're both Singha's men.

151
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,760
Sure, we're Singha's men.

152
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,600
But we're not loyal to him.

153
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:45,800
You know, that police number
was my uncle's.

154
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,400
And he got killed by them.

155
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:50,800
Really?

156
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,520
I want revenge on them just like you do.

157
00:14:58,320 --> 00:14:59,720
How about this?

158
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,000
We team up

159
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,160
and get revenge on Singha and Boss Noo.

160
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,800
What do you say? You in?

161
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,640
Answer me.

162
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,440
Are you going to work with the two of us?

163
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,400
Hey! What are you guys doing?!

164
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:27,560
Doing drugs or something?
I'll report this to Kamnan Pong!

165
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:29,800
Oh, well…

166
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,560
Shoot!

167
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,600
-Hey!
-Don't follow him.

168
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:39,680
Nothing, Uncle. No one's doing drugs.

169
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:44,160
Why not follow him?
What if he tells everyone about us?

170
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:51,480
He's being hunted too.
I don't think he'll say a word.

171
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:58,080
Let's split here.
I've got a meeting with Au.

172
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:10,120
See you.

173
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:16,360
I don't even know
how Uncle Tharin's doing.

174
00:16:16,440 --> 00:16:20,040
Yesterday, if he hadn't helped,

175
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,360
I probably would've been attacked
by those guys.

176
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:25,440
If you hadn't told me,
I wouldn't have known.

177
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,520
He never tells me anything.

178
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,240
I'll head off now, Puna.

179
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,040
Okay.

180
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,280
Chaiya?

181
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,360
Chaiya!

182
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,440
Oh, Puna.

183
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,520
Where were you yesterday?

184
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:56,080
Just out on a little mission.

185
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:02,480
Oh, right. I also ran
into your uncle yesterday.

186
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:08,200
Everyone seems to know
what Uncle Tharin was up to.

187
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,319
Even though we live in the same house,

188
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,040
he wouldn't tell me a thing.

189
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:20,680
I think that guy, Chart,

190
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:24,400
is still hung up on your uncle.

191
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,160
Do they have some issue?

192
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:32,640
Then let's ask him together. Are you free?

193
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:36,040
Yeah, but don't go to his house yet.

194
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:38,320
Can you call him to come somewhere else?

195
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:43,000
If not his house, then the cabin works.

196
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:45,480
Okay.

197
00:17:58,840 --> 00:17:59,760
Puna.

198
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,640
So it's you.

199
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,080
I'm Chaiya.

200
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:11,600
Thank you for yesterday.

201
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:13,760
Yes.

202
00:18:13,840 --> 00:18:16,400
So, who are you exactly?

203
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,640
Chaiya's my friend.

204
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:22,400
He works as Mr. Sonrak's driver.

205
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:25,760
Then why are you involved with Chart?

206
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:34,360
-Well…
-If you're involved with bad people,

207
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,920
even if you're a good person,

208
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,240
I can't fully trust you.

209
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,520
I understand.

210
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:47,760
But I swear on my honor as a man,

211
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:51,280
I'm definitely not like those evil people.

212
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:56,640
You're not a bad person,

213
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:59,680
but getting so close to bad people
that you become one,

214
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,600
it doesn't make sense.

215
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:13,080
Anyway, I appreciate your help.

216
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:18,080
But next time, don't come near us again.

217
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,160
Uncle.

218
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:33,360
Yes, but before I leave,

219
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,760
I want to give you some information.

220
00:19:40,640 --> 00:19:41,560
What information?

221
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:43,520
I don't know

222
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:46,440
what issues you and Singha have.

223
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:49,760
But yesterday I overheard them.

224
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:54,680
They're sending someone to watch you
because they suspect something.

225
00:19:59,560 --> 00:20:01,800
That's why I asked you two
to meet here today,

226
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:04,120
so they wouldn't know.

227
00:20:11,040 --> 00:20:12,760
Well, I'll take my leave now.

228
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:48,680
Why didn't you tell my uncle you're…

229
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:49,760
I can't.

230
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:51,720
It's a secret.

231
00:20:52,520 --> 00:20:54,000
You mustn't tell anyone either.

232
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,400
If this gets out,

233
00:20:57,480 --> 00:20:59,760
Manat and I could be killed.

234
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,040
I won't tell anyone.

235
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,880
Can you tell me

236
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:13,320
what your uncle and Singha
are involved in?

237
00:21:15,400 --> 00:21:16,600
I might be able to help.

238
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:22,560
It's probably connected
to the death of my parents.

239
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:25,760
If you want more details,

240
00:21:25,840 --> 00:21:29,920
look up news
about the singer Phupha and Onanong.

241
00:21:34,040 --> 00:21:36,760
Alright, I'll look into it.

242
00:21:49,520 --> 00:21:51,080
You need to be very careful.

243
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:56,320
You and your uncle might be in danger.

244
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,920
I'm worried.

245
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,280
Something happened yesterday,

246
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:35,920
and you didn't tell me.

247
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:42,280
I thought it was minor,

248
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:43,640
so I didn't.

249
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,080
Can you tell me

250
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:49,560
why Mr. Singha
ordered someone to watch you?

251
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:55,120
They probably think

252
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,680
your father and I switched places.

253
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,600
Switched places?

254
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,720
If that's what they believe,

255
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:08,680
they'd fear the police might reopen
the murder case they committed.

256
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:22,320
If you and my dad had switched places,

257
00:23:24,600 --> 00:23:26,280
maybe that would've been better.

258
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:29,960
Dad, you're here.

259
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:32,000
I'm not your dad.

260
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:36,320
You should call me Uncle.

261
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:39,560
I'm his identical twin.

262
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:47,200
Puna, how would it be better?

263
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:53,840
Then you'd be my dad.

264
00:23:55,320 --> 00:23:57,920
I'd finally have a father.

265
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,800
It's not the truth.

266
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:13,000
Hey, I'm your uncle,

267
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,120
not your dad.

268
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,040
Hm?

269
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,120
I know.

270
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,160
Alright. From now on,

271
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:26,920
wherever you go, you must be careful.

272
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:30,840
Most importantly,
don't go back to the house.

273
00:24:30,920 --> 00:24:32,400
Stay with Teacher Mueangphrai.

274
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:33,920
If anything happens,

275
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:37,840
you won't get caught in it. Understand?

276
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:40,360
Yes, Uncle.

277
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:16,160
Kamnan, Captain Tom is here.

278
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,080
-Send him in.
-Yes.

279
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:29,040
You had someone fetch me.
What's this about?

280
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:33,720
I want to collaborate with you.

281
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,280
Be direct, Kamnan.

282
00:25:39,360 --> 00:25:42,240
I don't have much free time.
I have a lot of work to do.

283
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:48,800
Captain, take a look at these.

284
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,280
Where did you get these photos?

285
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:01,720
Since you set up the checkpoint
for my donation truck,

286
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:04,680
I've been watching
the people around me constantly.

287
00:26:04,760 --> 00:26:06,120
That's how I discovered

288
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,120
they were breaking the law.

289
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,880
But now their influence is huge,

290
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:13,840
beyond what an officer
of your rank can handle.

291
00:26:14,480 --> 00:26:18,120
That's why I'm proposing a collaboration.

292
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:21,440
How exactly are we supposed
to work together?

293
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:25,680
Starting today,

294
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,600
I'll have my team

295
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:31,520
track all of their financial routes

296
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,200
and collect the evidence.

297
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:37,840
As for you, have your team focus

298
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:40,680
on tracing their drug operations.

299
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,360
They're following me.

300
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,440
I wonder who it is.

301
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:16,160
-Hey!
-Hey!

302
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:18,320
Den, Tu, go after her!

303
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,320
Hey, don't run!

304
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:24,520
Wait, go lock the car first,
or it'll get stolen.

305
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,920
-What?
-Hurry! Go after her!

306
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:29,120
What? Hey!

307
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:31,120
Go after her! Right now!

308
00:28:46,560 --> 00:28:47,880
Get her, Den!

309
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:52,000
What's this? Oh no!

310
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:56,520
Get her now! Grab her!

311
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,120
Hold her!

312
00:28:58,200 --> 00:28:59,760
Hey! Quick, Tu!

313
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:00,640
Hey, stop!

314
00:29:01,360 --> 00:29:02,560
Whoa!

315
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,240
Good thing my legs are steady.

316
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:05,360
Where are you going?

317
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,680
Just let us catch you!

318
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:07,880
No way!

319
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:10,000
-Ouch!
-Oh no!

320
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:12,280
Hey! Stop!

321
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:16,960
Why run and tire yourself out?

322
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:19,960
-Her?
-No, me!

323
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:20,880
Hey!

324
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:23,720
-Tu!
-Yeah?

325
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:24,600
Did you lock the car?

326
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:26,400
Did I lock it? Wait!

327
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:28,480
Why worry about the car now?

328
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,120
-Just catch her!
-Wait!

329
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:33,160
Who are you, and why
are you after me, uncles?

330
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:35,640
-You're calling us uncles?
-Hey, stop!

331
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:38,480
See? You guys are being rude!

332
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,840
How about seeing us
as older brothers, not uncles?

333
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:45,080
Cut the sweet talk.

334
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:46,680
Hey, stop wasting time!

335
00:29:46,760 --> 00:29:48,080
Grab her!

336
00:29:48,160 --> 00:29:49,200
-Come with us!
-Hey!

337
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:53,480
See? I warned you, but you didn't listen.

338
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,520
I said be polite!

339
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:55,440
Watch me!

340
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:58,120
Right? Take it easy and come with me.

341
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:00,280
No one will get hurt. Got it?

342
00:30:00,360 --> 00:30:01,520
-Let's go. See?
-Alright.

343
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:02,720
I'm not going.

344
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,760
-Let go!
-Ugh!

345
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:05,880
Hey!

346
00:30:05,960 --> 00:30:07,200
Take this!

347
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:11,640
Whoa. No one gets hurt, you say.

348
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:14,520
You've got no self-defense at all.
Look at you!

349
00:30:22,080 --> 00:30:22,960
Puna, don't!

350
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:34,920
I'm sorry.

351
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,440
I got scared.

352
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:39,440
I thought you were some pervert,
so I had to defend myself.

353
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:42,160
Wow, this is just self-defense?

354
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,360
I almost died.

355
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:46,240
-Oh no.
-You almost died?

356
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:48,160
-I only saw you running and huffing.
-What?

357
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:49,400
I'll break your teeth.

358
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:50,360
Enough!

359
00:30:51,280 --> 00:30:54,000
Ugh, what a mess.

360
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:56,760
Well, I'm sorry.

361
00:30:56,840 --> 00:31:00,800
These guys attacked and scared you.

362
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:02,080
It's okay.

363
00:31:02,680 --> 00:31:03,640
Really, sorry.

364
00:31:04,560 --> 00:31:06,600
-You three, come here.
-Yes.

365
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:11,440
Go see a doctor already!

366
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,760
-Always causing trouble.
-Oh.

367
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:16,880
-Here you go!
-Huh?

368
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,120
Wait.

369
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,960
-Why counting them then?
-Here.

370
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:21,560
Go now.

371
00:31:21,640 --> 00:31:22,600
-Now?
-Go!

372
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:23,720
Got it.

373
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:26,000
Still not leaving? Ugh.

374
00:31:27,640 --> 00:31:28,560
Alright.

375
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:31,000
How did this come about

376
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:33,000
that Boss Nok wanted to talk to me?

377
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:35,320
Nothing serious. It's just that my people

378
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,520
happened to hear you singing.

379
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:40,600
They told me, and I remember

380
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:45,240
watching you in the singing contest
with Darathong Music.

381
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:48,200
And that day,

382
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:49,720
you won first place, didn't you?

383
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:51,960
What's the matter?

384
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:55,480
Well, there's just one thing.

385
00:31:56,760 --> 00:32:02,120
The thing is, Teacher Mueangphrai told me

386
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:04,480
that after you won the contest,

387
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:06,640
you haven't worked on any songs yet.

388
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:09,320
So I wanted

389
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:13,680
to invite you to work with my company.

390
00:32:15,120 --> 00:32:17,120
Boss Nok owns a music label.

391
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:20,360
It's not as famous as Darathong Music,
but he's produced some work.

392
00:32:23,360 --> 00:32:27,160
Well, I wasn't planning
on joining only big labels.

393
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:29,920
But I already signed a contract,

394
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,080
so it's probably too late to change that.

395
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:34,800
Contract issues?

396
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,280
I'll handle that myself.

397
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,400
BAI TONG MUSIC

398
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:55,680
As soon as you agree,

399
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:58,720
Boss Nok will handle everything.

400
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:01,280
Hey, Miss Maria. This way.

401
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:02,280
Let's go.

402
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:07,320
Miss Maria, look! It's Puna.

403
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,920
What's she doing at Boss Nok's label?

404
00:33:11,880 --> 00:33:13,360
Is she switching labels?

405
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,000
It's fine if she switches labels.

406
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:19,000
That way, she won't steal
your spotlight anymore.

407
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:22,440
A small label like this
won't make her famous anyway.

408
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:25,160
But this is serious.

409
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:27,040
She'd be breaking her contract.

410
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:30,000
If Mr. Singha finds out,

411
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,280
she'll get punished for sure.

412
00:33:32,360 --> 00:33:33,360
Definitely.

413
00:33:33,440 --> 00:33:36,200
Quick, get your phone and film her.

414
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:38,640
Hurry up, Joey.

415
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:43,200
Smile, everyone. One, two…

416
00:33:43,280 --> 00:33:45,440
Hey, film her.
Why are you filming us instead?

417
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:47,440
Sorry, I forgot.

418
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:53,120
But I've already signed
with Darathong Music.

419
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:57,440
Switching now could cause
bad press, Teacher.

420
00:33:58,080 --> 00:33:59,760
You're right.

421
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:03,240
Let's see how Boss Nok and Singha react,
then we'll decide.

422
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:06,240
-Let's go.
-Okay.

423
00:34:22,239 --> 00:34:23,400
Uh…

424
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:25,920
What do we do?
Should we go tell Mr. Singha now?

425
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,679
Wait a bit, Miss Maria.

426
00:34:28,760 --> 00:34:31,400
If we storm in while he's in a bad mood,
we'll get into trouble.

427
00:34:32,199 --> 00:34:33,440
But we already have the proof.

428
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:34,440
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

429
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,960
Just hold onto it for now.
I'll handle this.

430
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:38,760
Don't act rashly.

431
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:41,679
Keep it casual. Don't draw attention.
Otherwise, others will notice.

432
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:44,080
Got it.

433
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:53,199
What should we do
with the video we recorded?

434
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:54,600
-Exactly.
-Come on, everyone.

435
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:56,159
Oh, the teacher is here.

436
00:34:56,679 --> 00:35:00,360
Miss Maria, let's start practicing now.
We're running late.

437
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,120
We just got here. Already practicing?

438
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:05,880
I have another session
with a different artist.

439
00:35:05,960 --> 00:35:08,720
If we don't start now, it'll be a loss.

440
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:11,000
Alright, fine.

441
00:35:11,680 --> 00:35:14,080
Miss Maria, you go ahead and practice.

442
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:16,880
I'll go handle some undercover work.

443
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,280
Okay.

444
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:20,160
Excuse me.

445
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:21,080
Come here.

446
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:22,800
Line up!

447
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:24,720
Hands on your hips.

448
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:26,040
One, two, three.

449
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:29,120
Left, left.

450
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,800
Hips, hips!

451
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:33,360
SONRAK DARATHONG

452
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,440
Oh!

453
00:35:38,520 --> 00:35:40,320
-Ice.
-Yes?

454
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:42,280
Is there a meeting today?

455
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:43,320
Yes.

456
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:44,280
What kind of meeting?

457
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:47,480
A commercial shoot
for Kamnan Pong's factory.

458
00:35:48,240 --> 00:35:50,560
-A commercial shoot?
-Yes.

459
00:35:51,160 --> 00:35:52,720
Oh, Puna!

460
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:55,400
Come quickly. The boss is waiting.

461
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:56,800
Okay.

462
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:03,800
-I'm back to work now.
-Okay.

463
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,760
Hello. Sorry I'm late.

464
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:20,040
Come on. Have a seat.

465
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,360
Let's get started.

466
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,720
-Sonrak.
-Yes.

467
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:36,480
Who's directing this?

468
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:38,640
Well, I was thinking…

469
00:36:39,520 --> 00:36:41,200
Chaiya, can you direct it?

470
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:45,120
The script isn't too difficult.

471
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:47,160
I can handle it.

472
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:49,720
Then I'll be Chaiya's assistant, right?

473
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:53,920
Keep the team small.

474
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:56,400
Use only company people, no outsiders.

475
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,320
Yes.

476
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:02,800
What about the actors?

477
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:10,320
I'll have Puna as the lead.

478
00:37:14,040 --> 00:37:15,280
Shoot!

479
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:17,920
ONANONG WONGWICHIAN

480
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:21,880
But I handle wardrobe, not acting.

481
00:37:21,960 --> 00:37:24,680
I want to save as much budget as possible.

482
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:26,520
You take this role.

483
00:37:26,600 --> 00:37:28,320
Do both wardrobe and act.

484
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:33,480
But I'm not sure I can do it well.

485
00:37:33,560 --> 00:37:35,280
You have to make it work.

486
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:45,520
Don't worry, Puna. I'm the director.

487
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:47,760
I'll guide you to make it work.

488
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,320
Hey.

489
00:38:05,400 --> 00:38:06,760
What?!

490
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:08,800
Puna's getting to shoot a commercial?

491
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:10,560
-Yes.
-What?

492
00:38:10,640 --> 00:38:11,880
Is something going on here?

493
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:14,520
-No, nothing at all.
-No.

494
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:18,560
Teacher, can I take a short break?

495
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:21,680
Sure, I'll head to the restroom then.

496
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:22,680
Okay.

497
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:26,720
Hey, what did you hear?
Tell me everything.

498
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:28,800
I heard it loud and clear.

499
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:32,280
They're planning to have Puna
in the commercial.

500
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:34,200
-She's going to be the lead.
-Geez!

501
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:36,160
Hey, we can't let that happen, Miss Maria.

502
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:37,360
Absolutely not!

503
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,480
That's right!

504
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:41,920
If Puna shoots this commercial
and becomes famous,

505
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:43,960
you'll be totally overshadowed.

506
00:38:44,040 --> 00:38:46,560
No, I won't let that happen!

507
00:38:47,680 --> 00:38:50,280
Let's figure out together what to do.

508
00:38:51,920 --> 00:38:53,880
I really want to be in this commercial.

509
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:56,600
Do whatever it takes
so I can get the role.

510
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,400
Then we need a plan.

511
00:39:04,280 --> 00:39:05,920
Alright.

512
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:06,920
Okay.

513
00:39:08,720 --> 00:39:10,600
Sit down slowly, Boss.

514
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,040
Damn it!

515
00:39:16,120 --> 00:39:18,000
How did they find out our plan?

516
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:19,720
Could one of our people be a mole?

517
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:21,400
What do you think, Khod?

518
00:39:22,680 --> 00:39:24,360
Doesn't seem like it, Boss.

519
00:39:24,440 --> 00:39:26,000
We've been together a long time.

520
00:39:26,680 --> 00:39:28,840
No one would betray you.

521
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:39,360
Any news, Pleaw?

522
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:43,160
Singha's movements, Boss

523
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:54,200
I never expected Puna

524
00:39:55,880 --> 00:39:58,080
to be the heir of Phupha Thararin.

525
00:39:59,880 --> 00:40:01,560
It's her pain.

526
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:05,920
That's why she won't talk
about her parents.

527
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:09,400
The case of Phupha and Onanong
was big back then.

528
00:40:11,400 --> 00:40:14,560
Back then, the media
mixed gossip into the reports,

529
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:18,320
tarnishing the victims' reputations.

530
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:19,720
You're right.

531
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,680
But why has Uncle Tharin

532
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:25,640
stayed silent for over 20 years?

533
00:40:25,720 --> 00:40:27,760
Didn't fight, didn't reopen the case,

534
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:30,120
even though his brother was killed.

535
00:40:30,200 --> 00:40:31,280
If it were me,

536
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:34,760
with a brother murdered
under suspicious circumstances,

537
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:37,280
I'd hunt them down

538
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:40,080
and uncover the full truth.

539
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:43,160
But from what I know,

540
00:40:44,040 --> 00:40:46,320
Uncle Tharin's always been
weak and sickly,

541
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,440
never able to fight,

542
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:50,000
unlike his late brother.

543
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:51,520
What does that mean?

544
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:54,200
Maybe that's why.

545
00:40:55,480 --> 00:40:57,640
He seems so weak,

546
00:40:57,720 --> 00:40:59,720
afraid he might get hurt

547
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:03,200
and unable to protect his own niece.

548
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:05,480
That makes sense.

549
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:11,840
Looks like Singha and Kitti

550
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:14,880
are behind this crime.

551
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:16,520
Otherwise, they wouldn't be nervous

552
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:19,560
and send people to watch Puna's uncle.

553
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:20,760
What are they afraid of?

554
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:23,640
Probably that the truth will come out.

555
00:41:23,720 --> 00:41:25,960
I'll help Puna investigate this.

556
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:31,000
Excuse me, Captain.

557
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:34,080
Another report just came in.

558
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:35,240
About what?

559
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:40,920
Besides hiding drugs in the dry cleaner,

560
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,320
they've also stashed some

561
00:41:42,400 --> 00:41:44,360
at Kamnan Pong's
agricultural processing factory.

562
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:49,480
Hey, we have an ad shoot there tomorrow.

563
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:51,840
Should we use the chance to check?

564
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,640
Perfect.

565
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:57,840
Just make sure to record
everything for evidence.

566
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:02,320
DARATHONG MUSIC

567
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:05,480
Sorry for making you wait, Teacher.

568
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:06,640
What's all this for?

569
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:10,280
I need to prepare clothes
for the villagers who will be acting too.

570
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:12,160
They're really putting you to full use,

571
00:42:12,240 --> 00:42:15,080
both acting and doing wardrobe.

572
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:17,920
It's okay, Teacher.
Just a little. I can handle it.

573
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:21,400
I'm glad you got an ad job.

574
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:23,960
At least, even if you're not singing,

575
00:42:24,040 --> 00:42:26,000
people still get to know you.

576
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:29,360
Yes, Teacher. Once my contract ends,

577
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:31,640
I'll probably focus on YouTube.

578
00:42:31,720 --> 00:42:32,800
Good idea.

579
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:35,160
Today's shoot is at the factory, right?

580
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:36,080
Yes.

581
00:42:36,160 --> 00:42:37,440
Then let's get in the car.

582
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:39,200
-I'll help you.
-Thank you.

583
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:41,960
-Oops, be careful.
-Yeah.

584
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:55,720
Get in the car.

585
00:43:09,960 --> 00:43:12,920
There's no way
you're filming that ad, Puna.

586
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:20,280
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

587
00:43:20,880 --> 00:43:24,600
Time to inspect the factory.
If you see anything suspicious,

588
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:25,960
record it immediately.

589
00:43:26,040 --> 00:43:28,480
Got it. Where should I put this?

590
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:31,120
Just put it right here.

591
00:43:40,360 --> 00:43:42,560
Tod, Wong, you two made it fast!

592
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:46,160
Have you guys found the right angles yet?

593
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:48,200
I saw you walking around.

594
00:43:48,280 --> 00:43:50,600
Yeah, we're checking out the angles.

595
00:43:50,680 --> 00:43:52,160
We need to try a few spots

596
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:54,240
and see which one works best.

597
00:43:54,320 --> 00:43:56,040
-Really?
-Yes.

598
00:43:57,880 --> 00:43:58,760
By the way,

599
00:43:59,920 --> 00:44:02,120
you two look good.

600
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:03,680
We should put you in the scene.

601
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:05,280
What the heck?

602
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:08,360
Right now, I need a lot more extras.

603
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:09,400
-Really?
-Yes.

604
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:11,320
-You're right, Chaiya.
-Yeah.

605
00:44:11,400 --> 00:44:12,840
Wow!

606
00:44:12,920 --> 00:44:14,760
You guys are perfect on camera.

607
00:44:15,360 --> 00:44:16,320
-When you're on camera,
-He's filming?

608
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:17,880
your aura really shows.

609
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:19,760
Wait, aren't you

610
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:21,840
flattering us too much?

611
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:25,760
Not at all. Come check it yourself.

612
00:44:25,840 --> 00:44:27,160
-Come here.
-Really?

613
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:28,200
Show me.

614
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:32,440
Hey, you guys!

615
00:44:32,520 --> 00:44:33,600
What's wrong?

616
00:44:37,160 --> 00:44:38,960
Sharp eyes, huh?

617
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:41,600
-Hey, shoot more!
-We're looking good!

618
00:44:41,680 --> 00:44:42,680
Yeah!

619
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:44,560
-That works!
-We're doing fine.

620
00:44:45,160 --> 00:44:46,240
-Wow!
-Hey!

621
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:47,400
-Keep shooting!
-Shoot more!

622
00:44:47,480 --> 00:44:48,360
-Closer.
-So handsome.

623
00:44:48,440 --> 00:44:49,880
Hello!

624
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:52,320
Is this the ad shoot location?

625
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:55,280
Oops!

626
00:44:56,640 --> 00:44:57,720
Yes.

627
00:44:57,800 --> 00:44:58,960
-That's right.
-Oh, it's here.

628
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:00,720
Let me introduce myself.

629
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:02,640
I'm Sis Haan.

630
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:04,240
My nickname's Haan.

631
00:45:04,320 --> 00:45:05,840
-My real name's Haan!
-Oh!

632
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:09,880
I'm the makeup artist for the actors.

633
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:11,040
I see.

634
00:45:11,120 --> 00:45:13,280
May I ask which actors

635
00:45:13,360 --> 00:45:14,520
should I be doing makeup for?

636
00:45:15,400 --> 00:45:16,200
-Which one?
-Oh.

637
00:45:16,280 --> 00:45:17,560
-These two, sis.
-Us?

638
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:18,880
Exactly, these two.

639
00:45:18,960 --> 00:45:20,680
-These two? Ooh!
-Yes.

640
00:45:20,760 --> 00:45:22,760
Handsome and buff, wow!

641
00:45:22,840 --> 00:45:24,280
Just my type!

642
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,120
I'll do your makeup,

643
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:27,840
giving you the kick-ass service!

644
00:45:27,920 --> 00:45:29,760
You mean give us
a fully handsome look, right?

645
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:31,080
-I'll kick you like this.
-Oh!

646
00:45:31,640 --> 00:45:32,840
-Just kidding!
-Okay.

647
00:45:32,920 --> 00:45:35,280
Once your makeup is done,
we should go out and kick up our heels.

648
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:36,320
Okay.

649
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,360
Are you ready?

650
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:39,840
-Let's start with these two.
-Start with us?

651
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:40,760
-These two?
-Yes, take them.

652
00:45:40,840 --> 00:45:41,960
-Ready?
-They're ready.

653
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:43,640
If you're ready, go ahead.

654
00:45:43,720 --> 00:45:44,680
Go ahead. This way.

655
00:45:44,760 --> 00:45:46,120
-This way.
-Go ahead.

656
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:47,400
-Stop posing so much.
-Wow!

657
00:45:47,480 --> 00:45:48,680
Looking good, Tod!

658
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:50,960
Yeah, go ahead.

659
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:53,000
Make them really handsome,
and take your time!

660
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:56,480
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

661
00:46:16,400 --> 00:46:18,240
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

662
00:46:21,280 --> 00:46:24,080
UNINSPECTED, DO NOT OPEN!

663
00:46:25,560 --> 00:46:26,480
Manat.

664
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:35,680
There's definitely something in here.

665
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:37,160
Let's check it out.

666
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:40,040
Hey! Don't touch that!

667
00:46:46,560 --> 00:46:48,560
We just saw this spot looks perfect,

668
00:46:48,640 --> 00:46:51,920
so we wanted to move these boxes out
and set up the camera here.

669
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:58,800
You guys, move these boxes out of the way.

670
00:46:58,880 --> 00:46:59,920
They'll get in the way
while they're working.

671
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,440
Come on. Move them out.

672
00:47:01,520 --> 00:47:02,520
Move them out.

673
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:06,280
How's it looking? Is it okay?

674
00:47:06,360 --> 00:47:08,280
Let me try setting up the camera first.

675
00:47:10,240 --> 00:47:11,960
Why so complicated, huh?

676
00:47:12,040 --> 00:47:14,120
If you want a good shot,

677
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:15,840
you need the right angle.

678
00:47:17,160 --> 00:47:18,840
We all have our own expertise.

679
00:47:18,920 --> 00:47:19,920
Leave it to the younger crew.

680
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:22,160
They might do it well.

681
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:24,080
Let's go over there.

682
00:47:33,640 --> 00:47:36,200
-Sis, make me handsome.
-Don't worry.

683
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:38,080
You're in good hands.

684
00:47:38,160 --> 00:47:39,800
Oops, I forgot to tell you.

685
00:47:39,880 --> 00:47:42,320
-Tell me.
-I also take side jobs.

686
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:44,040
-Side jobs? What kind?
-Yes.

687
00:47:44,120 --> 00:47:45,000
Off-hours.

688
00:47:45,080 --> 00:47:47,120
Huh? Offroading?

689
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:48,400
Offroading? The hell
are you talking about!

690
00:47:50,320 --> 00:47:52,080
Sorry, my bad.

691
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:54,760
-I got carried away.
-Okay, your side gigs.

692
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:56,120
Yes, I have side jobs.

693
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:57,840
Wow, nice lips you've got there!

694
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:04,240
How's it going? All set?

695
00:48:06,240 --> 00:48:07,080
Yes, all set.

696
00:48:09,360 --> 00:48:12,080
Hey, what's this?
You going to be in the scene too?

697
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:19,560
Well, the director

698
00:48:19,640 --> 00:48:21,840
wants good-looking people for the scene.

699
00:48:22,440 --> 00:48:23,280
Yeah.

700
00:48:25,920 --> 00:48:27,280
-Really?
-Yes.

701
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:31,720
And Puna's not here yet?

702
00:48:32,240 --> 00:48:35,000
No, not yet. Since I got here,

703
00:48:35,080 --> 00:48:36,480
I haven't seen her.

704
00:49:03,520 --> 00:49:06,040
Teacher! Teacher!

705
00:49:19,120 --> 00:49:21,000
Really, I was being set up.

706
00:49:21,080 --> 00:49:22,360
I told you to leave!

707
00:49:22,440 --> 00:49:24,440
You have to get close to Mr. Sonrak.

708
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:27,320
Find a way to get to his house
for that bear.

709
00:49:27,400 --> 00:49:30,240
Nowadays, sweet singers don't really sell.

710
00:49:30,960 --> 00:49:33,000
I can see you have
a good voice and potential,

711
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:35,720
so I want to give you a chance.

712
00:49:38,320 --> 00:49:40,120
Puna is going to move

713
00:49:40,200 --> 00:49:42,440
and become a singer at Boss Nok's label.

714
00:49:42,520 --> 00:49:43,720
What?

715
00:52:43,440 --> 00:52:45,720
